Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.63,0:00:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, we're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.63,0:00:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have Hattori sit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.99,0:00:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.09,0:00:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he had some things to talk about, like the contract and the assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.64,0:00:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.03,0:00:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congrats on the serialization!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.31,0:00:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is someone else here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.90,0:00:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it have something to do with the contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.26,0:00:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Miura. I've been with Jack since last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.72,0:00:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.52,0:00:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.07,0:00:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.00,0:00:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura will be supervising you two from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.55,0:02:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.47,0:02:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already have a place to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.96,0:02:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.39,0:02:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got it from a relative who's a manga artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.65,0:02:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? How's the rent?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.83,0:02:43.02,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawaguchi Tarou's workplace, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.37,0:02:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really cheap; about as much as the utility bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.98,0:02:46.56,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could have rented a room with your signing bonus, but you've saved yourselves the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.90,0:02:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.44,0:02:52.04,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.36,0:02:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be in such a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.50,0:02:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we have to discuss the transfer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.16,0:02:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.97,0:03:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I mentioned earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Detective TRAP{\i0} will be supervised by Miura, not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.69,0:03:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in charge of other serializations\N and also just took over One Piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.68,0:03:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be a good idea just to\N hand off these two to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.22,0:03:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he was assigned to this new project.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.49,0:03:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we've been in this together until now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.41,0:03:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there absolutely no way you can do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.75,0:03:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.86,0:03:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't uncommon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.94,0:03:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little while ago, even a veteran author had their supervisor switched on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.13,0:03:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They protested to their editors, but were convinced eventually. {He?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.46,0:03:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.69,0:03:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably wouldn't even listen\N if new guys like you complained.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.19,0:03:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! I'll do my best! Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.02,0:03:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be in your care.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.62,0:03:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take care of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.55,0:03:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.48,0:03:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get going, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.29,0:04:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to keep a serialization going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best, Ashirogi Muto!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.52,0:04:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura, I'll leave them to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.65,0:04:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori sure is cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.01,0:04:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may not be unusual for this to happen, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.86,0:04:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.45,0:04:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, he was begging so desperately to be allowed to work on Ashirogi Muto, they got angry with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.87,0:04:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.24,0:04:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.45,0:04:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.36,0:04:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better show me a good manga!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.37,0:04:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.33,0:04:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.28,0:05:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle said it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.73,0:05:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do anything about an editor change, and getting used to one takes a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.71,0:05:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the reality of being a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it bothers me that supervisors are like lottery tickets; you could end up with a winner or a loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori was definitely a winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.29,0:05:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, am I a loser?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.56,0:05:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.49,0:05:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.40,0:05:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still only 23!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.87,0:05:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's combine our youthful spirits and go for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.73,0:05:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That much?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.73,0:05:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our contractual salary is that high?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.34,0:05:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too much for you high schoolers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.88,0:05:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you needed a place to work, we'd give you more money, but you guys already have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.43,0:05:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're not actually getting that amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.57,0:05:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, your script payment is ¥12,000 per page, with a 50% color page bonus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.26,0:05:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But I heard it was ¥9,000 for new authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.14,0:05:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's for non-serialized work. For serializations, it's ¥12,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.09,0:05:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, stop interrupting and listen. These are the arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.31,0:05:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.52,0:06:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The copyright belongs to Yueisha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.90,0:06:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No other magazine may publish your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.85,0:06:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have the leisure to draw for another magazine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.47,0:06:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite the opposite - since our annual contract is with you, I want to make sure it runs continuously for the whole year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.86,0:06:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.38,0:06:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring a proper contract next time, so you can sign it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.47,0:06:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.77,0:06:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's also the problem of your assistants,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.27,0:06:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I managed to get a pro named Ogawa. He's talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have many new people, so I've got no other talented people to give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.96,0:06:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have anyone you know who could help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who dabbles in manga or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.17,0:06:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Acquaintances?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.79,0:06:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishizawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.77,0:06:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having someone assist you with the\N inking and tone would help a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.45,0:06:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Miyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.50,0:06:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's our last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.20,0:06:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, I'll handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find two young people with serious personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.90,0:06:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.66,0:06:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, how much does it cost for an assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.90,0:06:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:06:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A young assistant costs ¥10,000 per day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.83,0:07:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About ¥160,000 per month working four days per week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.01,0:07:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the most, Ogawa would cost you ¥380,000 per month.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,¥380,000?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.99,0:07:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These days, you can only pull people in with that kind of salary, so it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.57,0:07:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It requires a high skill level, and he'll direct and supervise the other assistants for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.88,0:07:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, assistants have expenses like travel and food.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.36,0:07:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until it's published, we're in the red!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.00,0:07:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it gets canceled before then, we'll stay in the red!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.49,0:07:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't talk about being in debt when we've just been serialized.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.60,0:07:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.41,0:07:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, is it alright if they stay over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.10,0:07:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only enough space in the next room to nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.82,0:07:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle did a gag manga, so the assistants just went home the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.45,0:07:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your uncle was successful enough\N for assistants? What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.15,0:07:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name's Kawaguchi Tarou...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.57,0:07:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.03,0:07:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The author of that {\i1}Super Hero Legend {\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.54,0:07:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.58,0:07:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why that poster's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.58,0:07:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.83,0:07:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that work was born here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:08:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really loved it when I read it in middle school!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.14,0:08:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so impressed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.29,0:08:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm expecting even more from you now that I know your uncle is Kawaguchi Tarou!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.08,0:08:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next comes the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.97,0:08:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deadline is two weeks before Jack goes on sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.85,0:08:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, two weeks before \Nthe Monday that the issue is released.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.91,0:08:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ideally, we want the finished \Nmanuscript by the Friday before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.62,0:08:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final deadline for {\i1}TRAP{\i0}  is February 4th.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.17,0:08:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first volume is 54 pages. The second is 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.41,0:08:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really only has to be 25, but  you wanted a bit more?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.53,0:08:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to turn that in as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.93,0:08:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to wait for the survey results for Volume 4 onwards, so we won't get into those yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.12,0:08:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fine with the assistants starting at the beginning of the year?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.92,0:08:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.19,0:08:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.01,0:08:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going through this so fast. Is this guy a winner?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't have you lose to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.54,0:08:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Hiramaru Kazuya of {\i1}Otters 11{\i0} is new, like us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.85,0:08:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.51,0:08:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't met him yet, but according to the editorial department, he quit his job as a salary man to do manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quitting an office job?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.61,0:09:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that at the age of 26, he suddenly quit his job and started drawing manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.25,0:09:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without having read much manga before then, his first work got honorable mention in a monthly contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.29,0:09:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A genius on another level like Niizuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great things are expected from him more than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.24,0:09:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.17,0:09:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than Eiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.99,0:09:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.07,0:09:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Otters{\i0} is like a gag manga,\N and it has a different writing style.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.72,0:09:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, there's no use comparing\N different manga with each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.16,0:09:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that matters is that yours is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.23,0:09:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.21,0:09:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.77,0:09:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll give it our all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.82,0:09:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! You guys are still young!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.14,0:09:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna flare up and burn out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.18,0:09:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, we don't want to burn out...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.09,0:09:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that was a slip of the tongue. Don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he a winner or loser?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.17,0:09:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't seem like a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.23,0:09:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.29,0:09:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,January 17th is the New Year's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New Year's party?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.41,0:09:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we invited too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.66,0:10:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All serialized manga authors attend!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.30,0:10:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If authors don't attend without a good reason, the editors in charge of them won't have it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New Year's party...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.42,0:10:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy, but nervous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.17,0:10:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a problem of being nervous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.15,0:10:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, a car will be coming to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.10,0:10:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.37,0:10:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A car's picking you up, huh? Serialized manga authors are pretty amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's our meeting with the\N assistants. I'm kind of nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.31,0:10:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't I come then?  I could do odd jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.84,0:10:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd calm down if a girl was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.85,0:10:31.61,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There will only be men working today; five of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a man's workplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.21,0:10:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be different from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.21,0:10:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. I'll refrain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.37,0:10:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the chief assistant, Ogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.71,0:10:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.24,0:10:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is Kato.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.88,0:10:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in your care.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.16,0:10:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.04,0:10:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't say anything about a girl coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.18,0:11:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kato only lives 3 train stops from\N here. She won't be staying the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she has a year of experience as an\N assistant in both shoujo and shounen manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.16,0:11:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't find another person with that much experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.14,0:11:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.62,0:11:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll get distracted if there's a girl here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.15,0:11:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silly young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it! But my girlfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.01,0:11:15.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.65,0:11:15.91,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we get Miyoshi to do the inking?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.26,0:11:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's Takahama. He's 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.74,0:11:23.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of the people under me, he's the best at drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.97,0:11:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He avoided my gaze!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.88,0:11:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He works fast and has unlimited potential as an assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.63,0:11:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean he has no experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, Ogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.16,0:11:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.57,0:11:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're short one desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.19,0:11:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a tracer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.02,0:11:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The copier is old, but it looks like it will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, where is the computer and printer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.39,0:11:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.08,0:11:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.64,0:11:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are quite a few reference books here,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.76,0:11:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's best for {\i1}Detective TRAP {\i0}'s\N backgrounds to be realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.49,0:11:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to take pictures of scenery with a digital camera, edit and trace them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.50,0:11:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. I'll arrange it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:11:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.73,0:12:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you already have a penned-in manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.09,0:12:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tako, Takahama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.67,0:12:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finish up one page each.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.97,0:12:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, matching their art, draw other characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.23,0:12:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.79,0:12:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome! So this is a pro assistant!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.63,0:12:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.93,0:12:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.77,0:12:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you weak at drawing right-facing faces?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.58,0:12:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I sketch them in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.02,0:12:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.97,0:12:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of that, look at the whole manuscript in reverse and check for deviances.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.07,0:12:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though you're good at it, a little discrepancy stands out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.93,0:12:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do most of the backgrounds and spread the work among the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.38,0:12:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll leave the characters to Takahama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.73,0:12:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finishing will be done by the person with less work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.77,0:12:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura, if the first volume is 54 pages, and the second is 27,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.54,0:12:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should turn this in soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.01,0:12:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's really great!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.37,0:12:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to work hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.86,0:12:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our first serialization!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.12,0:13:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I borrowed my brother's suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.35,0:13:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like a salary man. I'm going in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.67,0:13:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.61,0:13:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said to come in everyday clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.51,0:13:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't take that seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.35,0:13:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's rude to greet the authors without wearing appropriate clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.22,0:13:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.37,0:13:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the Ashirogi residence?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.27,0:13:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.96,0:13:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be assisting you today. I'm Tanaka from Metropolitan Transportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.19,0:13:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.77,0:13:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already been waiting for 15 minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.07,0:13:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he got here early to avoid being late!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.75,0:13:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad for making him wait, so let's hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.70,0:13:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are Ashirogi, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.22,0:13:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please step inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.23,0:13:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.31,0:13:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we leave now, we'll get there 40 minutes early.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.65,0:13:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can arrange for us to arrive at a more suitable time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.45,0:13:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:14:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well then, we would like to arrive 15 minutes early.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.82,0:14:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.55,0:14:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being driven around like this makes me feel extra nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.73,0:14:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, I need to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.20,0:14:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Greetings. My name is Takagi of the pair of authors under the name Ashirogi Muto,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.69,0:14:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,creators of the manga Detective TRAP\N which will begin serialization in February.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.89,0:14:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.16,0:14:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it kind of long?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.08,0:14:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can just finish with "I'm Mashiro".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.93,0:14:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.25,0:14:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should talk too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way, it's not my thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.50,0:14:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.30,0:14:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this gathering of suspicious black cars?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.35,0:14:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.90,0:14:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.03,0:14:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have any belongings, you\N may leave them in the cloak room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take this number card with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.04,0:14:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.50,0:14:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura, Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:14:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness. I feel kind of out of place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.06,0:15:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is some place!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.97,0:15:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your serialization continues,\N you'll come here every year!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.13,0:15:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.31,0:15:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma is already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.87,0:15:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinohara! It's been a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.75,0:15:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, really out of place...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.09,0:15:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ashirogi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.95,0:15:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a belated "Happy New Year!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in his usual sweats!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.45,0:15:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minors mustn't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.66,0:15:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's plenty of juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.42,0:15:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is also juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.06,0:15:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.53,0:15:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.54,0:15:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there an editor who looked like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.42,0:15:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my new friend, Hiramaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.59,0:15:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiramaru?! That's him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:43.23,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,You just randomly approached me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.88,0:15:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the genius who may even be better than Eiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you! We're Ashirogi Muto!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.81,0:15:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.34,0:15:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you classmates of his? Is it alright to bring friends to the New Year's party?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.38,0:15:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them are authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.71,0:15:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The artist and writer of Ashirogi Muto.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.73,0:16:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two in one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.12,0:16:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really. There are a lot of young manga authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.03,0:16:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that, sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.95,0:16:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I've come to a pretty strange place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.95,0:16:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot of delicious food.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.44,0:16:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I took a wrong turn. Not on the highway, but in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.98,0:16:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I can be a manga author.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.79,0:16:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"No way"? Didn't you want\N to become a manga author?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.96,0:16:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I want to? For a moment I did think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.76,0:16:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was briefly possessed by the idea, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.93,0:16:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, when I was tired of going to work, I picked up an edition of Jack and thought I could do it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, what the hell was I doing? I screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.95,0:16:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He thinks he screwed up even though he was serialized?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.24,0:16:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey you, bring me another!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.68,0:16:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.78,0:16:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what did you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.29,0:16:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just didn't want to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.41,0:16:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now I've got a monthly\N serialization. That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do people have to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.70,0:16:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to sleep and eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.75,0:17:01.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have been born as a panda in a zoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.27,0:17:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that why it's called {\i1}Otter 11{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Subconsciously, I think the otter in the aquarium is better off than a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.45,0:17:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiramaru, there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.96,0:17:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, it's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.49,0:17:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who flattered me by saying "You have talent" and "You're a genius!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.61,0:17:17.11,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Before the party gets going,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.10,0:17:18.35,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,let's talk about the problem spots in the third volume...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.44,0:17:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshitashi! Do you think it's good to be alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.51,0:17:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, lets go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.20,0:17:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The catchphrase of your third volume...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.96,0:17:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiramaru is kind of weird and interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.93,0:17:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.78,0:17:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about to start, so come up to the front...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.63,0:17:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, we were just hit by Hiramaru's bad mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.85,0:17:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad mood?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.61,0:17:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, he did say serialization was impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.17,0:17:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there are certainly people who are\N uncertain when they get serialized so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But once you start up, it'll all work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.35,0:17:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two will be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.81,0:17:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.55,0:17:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, everyone. Thank you all for taking time out of your busy schedules to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.22,0:18:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for allowing me to be your host for this New Year's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.75,0:18:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Aida Soichi, and I work in Shounen Jack's editorial department.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.59,0:18:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Champagne for the toast?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.23,0:18:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.05,0:18:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's pretend to drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.61,0:18:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.83,0:18:16.57,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, let's have a few words from Mr. Torishima of the Board of Directors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.23,0:18:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's who Arare-chan's Mashirito and S{\i1}uper Hero Legend{\i0}'s Torishiman are based on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.67,0:18:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Torishima.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.88,0:18:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Torishima was a model for chief\N editors while I was working there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was happy when he came up to me at the New Years party, asked "Who said you could put me in there?!", and strangled me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.81,0:18:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.90,0:18:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I'm at the same New Year's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.95,0:18:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we done already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.20,0:18:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another few words, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.51,0:18:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.61,0:18:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, continuing on,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.16,0:18:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask Akimoto to lead the toast on behalf of all the authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.21,0:18:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.66,0:18:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to eat a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.59,0:19:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma, you took too much-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.21,0:19:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's delicious-looking stuff over there too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.55,0:19:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you perhaps Ashirogi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.82,0:19:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.02,0:19:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Arai. My {\i1}Baked Cheese{\i0} manga is getting serialized the volume before yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.89,0:19:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. I'm Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.93,0:19:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Mashiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.97,0:19:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleased to make your acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.65,0:19:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are high schoolers, I hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.23,0:19:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.96,0:19:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its nice to be fresh-faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.81,0:19:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I was just thinking of taking them around to meet everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.03,0:19:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It's tough for newcomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.51,0:19:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.36,0:19:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oishi, can I talk to you for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.70,0:19:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.11,0:19:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manga should be interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.66,0:19:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,61!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.11,0:19:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 61!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.50,0:19:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone have Bingo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.89,0:19:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.91,0:19:41.24,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,It's number 61!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.24,0:19:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.42,0:19:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our first winner, Takagi. Which prize would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.86,0:19:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.46,0:19:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The special prize right off the bat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.99,0:19:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect, since the TV in our workplace is still analog.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.18,0:19:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being a manga author really is about\N hard work, self-confidence, and luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.22,0:20:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More like hard work, conceit, and luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.58,0:20:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe we've used up our luck with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.68,0:20:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.84,0:20:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you won't give the go ahead for an anime yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.90,0:20:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuujirou said that an anime will catch up to the manga soon, so I shouldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.09,0:20:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's unexpectedly cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.70,0:20:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma, will you give me your autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.64,0:20:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of my relatives is a fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.26,0:20:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Who should I make it out to?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.95,0:20:19.27,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma Eiji looks like he's having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.27,0:20:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he delaying an anime adaptation?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.16,0:20:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already become a real, serious manga author.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:26.29,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma! Talk to me more! Reassure me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.18,0:20:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we be like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.29,0:20:27.37,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.64,0:20:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be able to come here every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.00,0:20:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we'll definitely come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.63,0:20:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that, you need to work hard on your serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.81,0:20:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.96,0:20:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Have you gotten a bit used to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.09,0:20:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.36,0:20:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people here are really charismatic, and we got a bit overwhelmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.00,0:20:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a great opportunity. Enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.04,0:20:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you like, there's an after party, and an after-after party!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.71,0:20:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only one high schoolers should attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.09,0:20:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give them undue temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.67,0:20:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Editor-in-Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.85,0:20:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.05,0:21:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mashirito!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.59,0:21:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Mashiro and Takagi. Their serialization begins this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.44,0:21:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawaguchi Tarou.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.22,0:21:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to him was a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.30,0:21:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As someone who worked with him, I can only feel regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.19,0:21:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a man with guts. You could say that backfired on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.28,0:21:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.51,0:21:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to have the opportunity to serialize people like you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.23,0:21:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.99,0:21:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.06,0:21:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to do the things my uncle couldn't do, and the things he left undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.04,0:21:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he couldn't do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.81,0:21:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he left undone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.66,0:21:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he couldn't do was make a living off of manga alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.13,0:21:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he left undone was getting first place in the survey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.04,0:21:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How promising.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.75,0:21:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The best chance of getting first place in the survey is in the first year of serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.65,0:21:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Popular manga authors want to get the top spot {\i1}and{\i0} have a long-running series.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.22,0:22:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how long it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.49,0:22:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The possibility isn't zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.68,0:22:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than thinking that, you think the possibilities are infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.70,0:22:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of thinking "I'd like to make that a reality", you think "By my actions, I'll make it a reality".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.52,0:22:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that from some movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.36,0:22:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.91,0:22:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though the party is in full swing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.81,0:22:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.16,0:22:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.81,0:22:23.88,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,unfortunately it's about time to wrap things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.05,0:22:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.87,0:22:27.24,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,We reserved the hall for a short time...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.24,0:22:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.67,0:22:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number one on the survey?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.59,0:22:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending a text to Azuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.52,0:22:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't forget the determination I had today!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.47,0:22:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.60,0:24:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our serialization is about to start, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.24,0:24:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...our supervisor got changed, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.86,0:24:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.78,0:24:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki, why did you send that text?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.85,0:24:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What text?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.11,0:24:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Anthologies and Photo Albums"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.12,0:24:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is more important, dreams or reality?
